			"type": "text",
			"text": "Khoratamia phattharajani comes from the Early Cretaceous, with fossils found in the Khok Kruat Formation, Thailand. It is a small amiid, growing up to 40 cm in length. The generic name derives from the place name 'Khorat Plateau', where the fossils were found; and the genus name 'Amia'. The specific name derives from the Latinised middle name of Somdet Phra Phatthara Maharat, a title given to King Bhumibol Adulyadej, who was dedicated to research and support of farming of Nile tilapia in Thailand."
